HEADWORD: Pterichthys
<hw>Pte*rich"thys</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ wing + <?/ fish.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
Devonian fossil fishes with winglike appendages. The head and most of
the body were covered with large bony plates. See
<er>Placodermi</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

